<div class="comment-content">
<p>Ever since moving away from home, I&#8217;ve done my own popcorn in a huge pot. Usually I use things like curry powder, nutritional yeast (for a cheezy effect) and fresh-pressed garlic simmered in Earth Balance(vegan butter sub.) It&#8217;s amazing! One of my secrets though is flavoured salt. I take a good Celtic sea salt and grind it up in my spice grinder, after grinding things like coriander seeds or cardamom pods. It makes for a lovely flavour addition, and it cleans out my spice grinder! <img src='http://dinersjournal.blogs.nytimes.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>Blessings,<br />
Lyra<br />
